A .NET Temporal workflow runs a long activity, then cancels it explicitly using a linked CancellationTokenSource. The cleanup activity must run to completion even after cancellation. A developer writes this:

```csharp
[WorkflowRun]
public async Task RunAsync()
{
    try
    {
        await Workflow.ExecuteActivityAsync(
            (MyActivities a) => a.MyNormalActivity(),
            new() { ScheduleToCloseTimeout = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10) });
    }
    catch (Exception e) when (TemporalException.IsCanceledException(e))
    {
        await Workflow.ExecuteActivityAsync(
            (MyActivities a) => a.MyCancellationCleanupActivity(),
            new() { ScheduleToCloseTimeout = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(5) });
        throw;
    }
}
```

The cleanup activity is scheduled but immediately gets cancelled itself before it can complete. What is the root cause and what is the correct fix?
